Chiaki is the orphaned daughter of the Archangel Michael and a human woman. Ororon is a devil with a bounty on his head. Together, they struggle to stay alive as the battle between devils and the angelic order rage around them.
name: Volume 1

description: When bounty hunters descend on the Chiaki house a great battle erupts in which Ororon tries desperately to respect Chiaki's wishes that he not kill anyone. However, the attacks from his foes prove far too fierce, thus driving him to summon golems down to slaughter the lot of them. While the rest of the household find themselves locked in various other battles, Ororon, laden with the guilt of upsetting Chiaki, searches for Shiro and Lika, encountering a long the way ghouls that don the faces of Ororon's fallen comrades. As the battle ends - ushered to victory with the concerted help of Chiaki, Shiro, Kuro, Lika, Othello and Mitsume, a bounty hunter that Othello wants to recruit into his Blue Dragon Army - Ororon and Chiaki face each other again, the devil barely able to look into the angel's eyes, riddled with shame as he is. But before Chiaki is able to forgive him, a new threat emerges, Jano, the leader of a vicious bounty-hunting group. He is defeated easily by Ororon, but as the devil goes in for the kill, Chiaki deflects his attack.
name: Volume 2

description: As the city lay in ruins, God reveals to Chiaki that the devastation is her fault, Ororon's attack that she deflected away from the bounty hunter Jano having spurred her own latent powers into action. The implicit pacifist, Chiaki is horrified to learn that her very existence is responsible for such wide scale death and destruction. Ororon, an agent of death and destruction himself, attempts to comfort her, assuring her that none of it could be her fault, but nothing will allay her fear that something like this will happen again. But, while Chiaki deals with the nature of her existence, the Piti Pats ready themselves for a colossal battle. And elsewhere, Osero and Three Eyes have some unfinished business with each other to attend to. A classic manga epic of monsters, magic, relationship woes and existentialism continues it's wild ride in English! Chiaki has unleashed the power of the godhead that lurks inside of her, leveling a city in the process. Now, both Heaven and Hell are in the scramble to find her, but Ororon (the wayward King of Hell) and his rag tag clan has retreated into hiding with her comatose body. Having escaped the bounty hunters of hell, they must now face the vengeful Piti - Pat tribe and the manifestation of the Holy Spirit of the highest rank and office they've managed to conjure! But, wait there's more! Two side stories explore the tragic pasts of both Prince Othello - General of the Seiryu army - and the three-eyed bounty hunter, Mitsume. Comedy, philosophy, action! It slices! It Dices! Step back...Ororon the Devil's rolling through!
name: Volume 3

description: While Othello and his Blue Dragon Army face down the bounty hunter Mitsume and the Devil Oscar's forces, Oscar himself finds Ororon and his brood. Oscar has been trying to assassinate Ororon this entire time, fearing his younger brother's power and possible desire to ascend to the throne of hell. This time there is no escape and Oscar, insane with hatred and thirsty for pain, proceeds to murder Ororon very slowly, torturing the poor lovesick Chisaki who can only stand by and watch. Chisaki's friends attempt to attack Oscar to allow Chiaki time to escape, but to no avail. They fall at the hand of the powerful devil. But just as Oscar turns his fury to Chiaki herself, Ororon musters all his remaining power to summon a beast to kill Oscar before falling over dead himself before Othello could even arrive with his own army.
name: Volume 4

description: While the Emerald Gauntlets (junior and senior) are dealing with the extra-dimensional Emerald Ones, back on Earth, mysterious visitors from another world have arrived. What is their purpose here, and what will their plans for one of Earth's greatest heroes hold in store for his son - and for Julie, also known as '84?'

Rasl returns to his craft of stealing the world's most valuable paintings when he needs funds for his plans to thwart the Lizard Faced Man.
